      "content": "The first principle of Open-Source Capitalism demands new types of platforms -- public marketplaces where contributors, customers, and investors can interact transparently. Like Uber or Airbnb, these marketplaces optimize for liquidity and coordination, but with open governance and ownership. They serve as the coordination substrate for decentralized organizations.",
